Your Honor,

I stand before you today as Chloe Mills, a 24-year-old individual pleading guilty to the offense of affray. I take full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge the seriousness of the situation.

Upon discovering that my boyfriend had been unfaithful to me, I acted impulsively and went to the bar where he was with his friends. In my state of emotional distress, I threatened him to disclose the name of the other woman involved. I regretfully admit that I resorted to physical aggression by slapping him in the face.

During my encounter at the bar, my behavior grew confrontational, causing discomfort and fear amongst those present. I deeply apologize for the distressing atmosphere I created and for not handling the situation in a more composed manner. I understand the impact it had on the individuals present, and I am genuinely remorseful for my actions.

I would like to emphasize that this incident is an isolated event in my life. I have no prior criminal record, as this regrettable incident stands in stark contrast to the law-abiding life I have led up until now.

In an effort to address the underlying issues that contributed to my behavior, I have sought professional help through weekly therapy sessions. These sessions have been a crucial part of my personal growth, enabling me to better understand my emotions and develop healthier coping mechanisms.

I assure the court that I am committed to preventing a repetition of such behavior. I have realized the need for introspection and have taken the necessary steps to ensure that I respond to difficult situations in a more composed and controlled manner. I am fully dedicated to my own personal development and actively seek ways to improve as an individual.

As I stand before you today, I cannot emphasize enough how sorry I am for the distress I caused to those present at the bar. I understand the need to uphold the law and accept the consequences of my actions. However, I kindly ask the court to consider my plea in mitigation, as I acknowledge my guilt and the significant progress I have made in addressing the underlying issues that contributed to this incident.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.
